request.description:
WebSocket connection for real-time updates. No authentication required.

Example client code:
```javascript
const ws = new WebSocket('ws://localhost:3001');

ws.on('connect', () => {
  console.log('Connected to WebSocket');
});

ws.on('answer-ready', (data) => {
  console.log('New answer:', data);
});

ws.on('voting-started', (data) => {
  console.log('Voting started:', data);
});

ws.on('voting-complete', (data) => {
  console.log('Voting complete:', data);
});
```

Event Types:
- `answer-ready`: New answer available for a question
- `voting-started`: Voting period has begun
- `voting-complete`: Voting has ended with results
- `question-submitted`: New question submitted (optional)
- `stats-updated`: Platform statistics updated
